the first time you've heard this name.)

12
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:37,240
(Standings)

13
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,360
(B.S. Brothers,)

14
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,760
(also known as Bullsh*t Brothers,)

15
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:43,320
(the Pro League team
that just won't stay dead.)

16
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:46,040
(P'Pech from PECHTECH)

17
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:48,240
(saw our potential)

18
00:00:48,360 --> 00:00:49,880
(and decided to sponsor us.)

19
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,560
(Ever since then,)

20
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:56,040
(we've grown into
one of the Pro League teams.)

21
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:57,640
(And right now, I think...)

22
00:00:57,840 --> 00:01:01,280
(we are ready
to reach even higher ground)

23
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:04,280
(because this is
the golden age of B.S. Brothers.)

24
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,600
If you join the B.S. Brothers,

25
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:16,760
fame, money,

26
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:18,600
or the chance to join a world-class team

27
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,760
won't be far out of reach, right?

28
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:29,360
Me? Seriously?

29
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:34,280
What's with that face?

30
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:38,240
Are you seriously that shocked
with excitement?

31
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,600
Why do you want me
to join B.S. Brothers?

32
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,760
After playing with you that day,

33
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,040
I saw your potential.

34
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:53,240
B.S. Brothers is a team
of top-tier pros and beasts

35
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,440
who have god-tier skills.

36
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,240
Just like you.

37
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,960
If we had you on our team,

38
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,600
we'd definitely be even stronger.

39
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,880
But I'm not really interested
in any of that.

40
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,200
Maybe you should try
asking someone else.

41
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,080
No one else has caught my eye.

42
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:19,120
In my eyes,
there's only you, Derpy Kid.

43
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:27,360
- Who's gonna replace him in time?
- Yeah.

44
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,080
We have to submit the roster soon, too.

45
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,000
What are we gonna do?

46
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,120
What on earth are you guys doing?

47
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,160
How do you expect to win like that?

48
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:34,640
I told you to push! Push!

49
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,480
Which hero are you playing?

50
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,360
Wukong.

51
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,560
Wukong? Get out of my cafe. I hate him.

52
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,560
If you know you're gonna die,
heal up first.

53
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:45,320
Trying to show off
just to end up feeding.

54
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:46,560
Jeez.

55
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,520
Just go home.

56
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:49,280
You saw our skills, right?

57
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:51,880
- I was so cracked just then.
- I'm about to crack your faces now.

58
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,080
Get out of my cafe.

59
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,840
You guys played like total trash.

60
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:15,280
You can take some time
to think about it.

61
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,280
I'm not in a rush.

62
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,960
(Where is this person
you had in mind?)

63
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,360
(I have to submit the roster
by midnight tomorrow!)

64
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,240
You can give me your answer tomorrow.

65
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:32,840
What?

66
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,280
Tomorrow? So soon?

67
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,520
You said you weren't in a rush.

68
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,800
What do you want to eat? Salmon?

69
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:42,680
I just had...

70
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:45,200
You can always eat more.
My treat, okay?

71
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,240
See you tomorrow.

72
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:46,840
Adios.

73
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,560
P'Three... Wait, P'Three.

74
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:09,080
♪Birthday but with me♪

75
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:12,400
♪Every time, it's just me and me only♪

76
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:16,040
♪What's this feeling? I've got no clue,♪

77
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,120
♪Could it be I'm missing you?♪

78
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,600
♪(Am I missing you?)♪

79
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:24,280
♪Birthday but with me♪

80
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:27,680
♪Why is it always happening to me?♪

81
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:31,640
♪The more it happens, the more I see♪

82
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,840
♪Yeah, it must be♪

83
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,520
Are you asking Soh to join the team?

84
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:57,440
Yeah.

85
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,280
I am.

86
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,600
I have your permission, right, Arm?

87
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,320
I'm over here.

88
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,560
Oh...

89
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,640
Hey.

90
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,520
What's so funny? Come here.

91
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,000
Get closer.

92
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,160
What's going on?

93
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:11,560
I don't know.

94
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,640
So, what's the verdict?

95
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,360
Got an answer for me yet?

96
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:18,840
Hmm?

97
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:22,360
But judging by the look in your eyes,

98
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,520
I already know what your answer is.

99
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:30,480
Make me happy. Let me hear it.

100
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:31,760
I...

101
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,120
I think...

102
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,320
there are many players out there
better than me.

103
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,080
This guy's skills are actually insane.

104
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:43,760
The Pro League seems cool,

105
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,440
but I don't think
my skills are there yet.

106
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:56,120
(Hey, we need to
submit the roster by midnight!)

107
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:04,280
Getting into the Pro League
is a huge opportunity,

108
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,480
right, James?

109
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,200
I'm Arm.

110
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,400
When did you guys switch places?

111
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,200
We didn't even switch.

112
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,640
Exactly. Tell your friend

113
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:14,640
that he's turning down
an opportunity everyone is dying for.

114
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,560
Well, he's right.

115
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,440
Going pro comes with great benefits.

116
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,840
Girls will be screaming for you,

117
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,280
and if you have a lot of fans,

118
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,880
- you'll make a fortune from donations.
- Exactly.

119
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,080
That's not even including the salary.

120
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:32,080
Well said.

121
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,200
But the decision is yours.

122
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:35,680
Why would you say that?

123
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,840
Or...

124
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,120
are you not saying yes

125
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,280
because you don't like me?

126
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,360
No, why would you think that?

127
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,880
Well... I mean...

128
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:02,120
I challenged you to a match,
made you do a face reveal,

129
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,120
and even barged into your room.

130
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,440
I knew it.

131
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:24,880
Please don't cry, P'Three.

132
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,680
Don't cry.

133
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:28,920
It's not like that at all.

134
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,720
It's not that I don't like you.

135
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,480
Then what is it, Soh?

136
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:36,440
Or is B.S. Brothers
not as cool as other teams?

137
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,520
Uh...

138
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:44,240
Don't cry, P'Three.

139
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,400
(I'll get him today.)

140
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,120
It's not about you or B.S. Brothers.

141
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,720
It's about me.

142
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,520
And what is...

143
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,280
I just want to play games for fun.

144
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,080
I don't want to compete with anyone.

145
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,520
I'll go get some water.

146
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,560
Does anyone want anything?

147
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:32,640
What's the deal?

148
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,520
What's going on with him?

149
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,440
- You tell him.
- No, you!

150
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,200
One of you, come on.

151
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,560
I mean, Soh is shy as hell.

152
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,960
Plus, he's socially awkward as f*ck.

153
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,880
Breaking down his own walls

154
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,880
to stream and actually talk to people
is already a big step for him.

155
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:54,080
It's way more complicated
than you think.

156
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,240
I'll explain everything
when we have time.

157
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:58,840
Derpy Kid,

158
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,680
I'll have a glass
of butterfly pea lemonade,

159
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:01,360
mixed with orange juice.

160
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,880
Add some green soda, orange juice,

161
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,720
red soda,
and some chrysanthemum tea as well.

162
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,040
Just mix it all together.

163
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:06,720
Very good.

164
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,320
Now we've got time.

165
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,320
Well...

166
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,000
And now, we've reached

167
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,480
(36th Youth Block-Building Competition)
the final stretch

168
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:30,160
of the 36th Youth
Block-Building Competition.

169
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,600
But I must say

170
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:35,280
there's one team
that stands out above all others,

171
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:38,240
and that is Soh's team

172
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:40,880
as the captain of this team has been

173
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:44,160
the solo youth block-building champion

174
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:47,160
for three consecutive years.

175
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,760
He's the favorite
to win this competition.

176
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:55,640
Let's give all of the teams
a round of applause!

177
00:09:55,640 --> 00:10:03,600
- Soh! Soh! Soh!
- Soh! Soh! Soh!

178
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:13,560
- Soh! Soh! Soh!
- Soh! Soh! Soh!

179
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:18,680
Whoa, I can't believe...

180
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:23,200
that Soh has made a mistake
at the very last second.

181
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,640
It's okay. Stay focused.

182
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:30,000
Let's see how he handles this situation.

183
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:40,600
Sh*t!

184
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:41,960
Was it really that bad?

185
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:46,080
Playing games for fun and competing
are two different things.

186
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,640
The pressure is
on a whole different level.

187
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:48,960
For real, P'Three.

188
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,800
I'm not saying he will never say yes,

189
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:55,240
but to change the mind of someone
with such high walls,

190
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:57,040
you're gonna have to climb over them.

191
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,440
Can you guys be my ladder?

192
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,160
What ladder?

193
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:12,040
No matter how high those walls are,

194
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,920
I'll make it over them.

195
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,520
What the hell is this drink?

196
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,720
What was he pointing at?

197
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,440
Hey, Arm, we have
more shopping to do, right?

198
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:08,360
Shopping for what?

199
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,760
Oh, right! Yeah, yeah.

200
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,800
We're heading out then.

201
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,240
- Bye, P'Three. See you, Soh.
- Yeah, see ya.

202
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:17,080
- Bye-bye.
- Where are you going? Let me come, too.

203
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,280
Hey, Soh.

204
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:23,120
Soh...

205
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:24,520
Look...

206
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,840
I really want you on my team.

207
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:34,160
Though I know you have your reasons
for not being ready,

208
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:39,480
I still want you
to give me a chance anyway.

209
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,760
Just give me one day.

210
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:51,160
In just one day,
I'll make you open up to me.

211
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,120
If the day ends

212
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,600
and you're still saying no,

213
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,360
I won't bother you ever again.

214
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,560
I'll show you how I zoom.

215
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:28,320
Come on, I'll show you
how I drive in reverse.

216
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:32,160
- Shouldn't you watch the road?
- Oh, right.

217
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,000
Man, this engine is just too powerful.

218
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,880
Keep your eyes on me, alright?

219
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,400
- Keep your eyes on me.
- P'Three,

220
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,600
- Oh, right...
- watch the road.

221
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,640
Damn, this car is fast.

222
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,160
Let's go.

223
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,120
Go.

224
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:48,960
Whoa, you're driving with one hand?

225
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,080
Wow!

226
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,600
I'm an expert on this map.

227
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:54,360
I'm a pro. I've played it
since I was a kid.

228
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:55,800
Wait, where'd you go?

229
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,760
- I'm right here.
- Oh.

230
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,760
I've never lost a match in my life.

231
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,600
Now, press the buttons as they light up.

232
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,640
Just smash them real quick.

233
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,960
Hit them fast, okay?

234
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,120
If you're ready,

235
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:06,360
let's go!

236
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,240
Ouch, Soh!

237
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:17,600
Why does my hand...

238
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,120
Why can't I feel anything in my hand?

239
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,720
Is this the end
of my career as a player?

240
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,120
Hey, P'Three!

241
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,120
I'm definitely gonna break the record.

242
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,640
But it's almost at the highest.

243
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:43,120
Whoa.

244
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:46,200
I definitely wouldn't want
to mess with you.

245
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,480
Of course. You wouldn't.

246
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:50,400
Hey, want to give it a shot?

247
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:54,960
- Let's go.
- But I've never tried this.

248
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,280
Yeah, go for it.

249
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:04,880
I think it might be broken.

250
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,760
I... I think so.

251
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,640
Shall we try a different machine?

252
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:12,880
Okay.

253
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:21,800
Is this machine broken?

254
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,320
I'm sorry, P'Three.

255
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,480
I couldn't get the hang of it.

256
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:26,280
Hey,

257
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:27,560
no need to worry about it.

258
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,240
Gaming should be fun, man.

259
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,240
If you lose, you just play again.

260
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:32,840
Come on, let's try again.

261
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:37,280
I'm serious this time.

262
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,440
- Is the gun too powerful, P'Three?
- Yeah, it is.

263
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:48,440
- Yay!
- Yay!

264
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:07,560
Uh...

265
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,400
There's something in your hair.
Right here.

266
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:13,760
- Really?
- Yeah.

267
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:14,960
It's everywhere.

268
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,200
It's everywhere?

269
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:27,840
Wait...

270
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,400
P'Three,

271
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,960
this is so cute.

272
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:31,720
Go for it.

273
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:36,800
Anyway, can I borrow some tokens
from you?

274
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,560
I only have one left,
and I don't think it'll be enough.

275
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,760
I'm all out of them, too.

276
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:44,760
And I don't have any cash.

277
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:47,040
I'll go hit the ATM first.

278
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,160
Wait here, okay?

279
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,080
Just join our activity,

280
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:56,200
and you'll get tokens for free!

281
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,280
Hey, kids.

282
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:01,520
Give it a try. I got ten tokens!

283
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,600
- It's for real.
- Go for it.

284
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:10,200
♪Birthday but with me♪

285
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:17,080
I'm not really into freebies, though.

286
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:19,880
But since you want them,

287
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:20,800
I'll get them for you.

288
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:22,320
P'Three...

289
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,600
Come on, go, go, go!

290
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:27,480
Let's do this.

291
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,520
The rules are simple.

292
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:33,200
Just keep dancing
until the song is over.

293
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:34,360
You got it.

294
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,200
Don't worry. I've got this.

295
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:37,800
Dancing is a piece of cake for me.

296
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,720
Look at my hips. Watch my moves.

297
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:41,800
Ready? Let's do it.

298
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,440
Even better, if you play as a couple,

299
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,520
you'll get a special bonus
of twenty tokens.

300
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:47,960
You definitely don't like dancing.

301
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:48,880
Ten is enough anyway.

302
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:49,760
Come on, I'm ready.

303
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:54,960
I'll dance, too.

304
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:55,920
Whoa.

305
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,720
It's twenty tokens, you know.

306
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:00,560
Alright, let's hit it.

307
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:07,080
♪Birthday but with me♪

308
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:10,400
♪It always happens to me
every single time♪

309
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:13,800
♪Is this how it feels?
Huh? Is that right?♪

310
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,160
♪Thinking of me, aren't you?♪

311
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,600
♪(Thinking of me, aren't you?)♪

312
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:22,080
♪Birthday but with me♪

313
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:25,640
♪It happens to me every single time♪

314
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:29,680
♪The more it's like this,
the more certain I am♪

315
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:32,040
♪Mm, that's right♪

316
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:39,000
♪(That's right, that's right)♪

317
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:43,000
♪The more it's like this,
the more certain I am♪

318
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:45,120
♪Mm, that's right♪

319
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:56,120
- Here are your twenty free tokens.
- P'Three, the game's over.

320
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,760
Sir, here you go.

321
00:18:58,240 --> 00:18:59,000
Thank you.

322
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:02,920
Whoa, twenty tokens?

323
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,280
Yes, twenty.

324
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,720
If you hadn't joined me,
we would've only gotten ten.

325
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,960
- The game is over. Please step down.
- Oh, we can go now?

326
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,160
Wow, twenty tokens.

327
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,480
- Thanks.
- Let's go for the claw machine.

328
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,960
I thought you'd be too shy.

329
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:18,440
I thought so, too.

330
00:19:18,920 --> 00:19:20,840
I was hesitant and scared at first.

331
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:23,320
But now, I feel like
I've unlocked something.

332
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:25,400
Thank you, P'Three,

333
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,120
for taking me out
to do something this fun.

334
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,760
Playing games with you
really is a lot of fun.

335
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,600
Then come play with me again.

336
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,080
But...

337
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:42,640
about joining B.S. Brothers,
I'm not sure at all

338
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:44,880
if I'll be good enough.

339
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,040
And I'm not even sure
if I'll fit in with the others.

340
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,280
I'm just not sure about anything now.

341
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,240
If you think you're not good enough,

342
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:56,440
I'd have to disagree

343
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,680
because the person
who beat me in that match

344
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,760
definitely doesn't have trash skills.

345
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,160
I can guarantee that.

346
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:06,920
As for whether you'll fit in or not...

347
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:08,920
Well...

348
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:12,720
If you think it's too hard,

349
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:14,320
just think of it as a game.

350
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:17,120
A super tough level
that you have to clear.

351
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,440
I believe that if it's about gaming,

352
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,840
you can definitely beat it.

353
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,640
Just like when you got up there
and danced with me.

354
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:34,080
So, while we're at it,

355
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:35,880
let's make a bet.

356
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:43,080
Look. If I win this plushie,

357
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,360
you have to join B.S. Brothers.

358
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,840
Deal. Let's bet.

359
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:04,480
Come on.

360
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:08,520
There it is.

361
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:10,480
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

362
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:10,920
Oh...

363
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:16,360
I'm just showing you it's there.

364
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:21,320
Is this machine rigged?

365
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,800
It's literally stealing my money.
What the hell?

366
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:26,000
I thought you said
games are supposed to be fun.

367
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,760
It's a real blast.

368
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:31,600
Whoa, whoa!

369
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:40,400
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

370
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,240
This is it.

371
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:49,920
Hey, hey, hey!

372
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:52,920
Blow on it.

373
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:56,840
Go.

374
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,760
(Game over)

375
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:12,840
As promised...

376
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:16,120
I won't nag you about this anymore.

377
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,120
Wait, P'Three.

378
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:29,560
I still have one token left.

379
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:47,480
Come on.

380
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,280
I really want to
play on the same team as you.

381
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,000
Come play with me.

382
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:16,000
Hey, P'Three!

383
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,080
Whoa, whoa!

384
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,840
- Whoa, wait!
- P'Three!

385
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:29,440
I got it.

386
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:34,520
But...

387
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:38,240
I have two conditions.

388
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:39,520
Sure thing.

389
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,920
Tell me as many as you want.
I'll agree to anything.

390
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,320
First,

391
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:46,920
every time we compete,

392
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:50,800
I get to wear my bear head
while playing.

393
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,360
Second,

394
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:57,120
if I feel like I can't do it
and want to withdraw,

395
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:01,200
please respect my decision.

396
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,680
Of course. No problem at all.

397
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:09,080
Welcome to B.S. Brothers, Derpy Kid.

398
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:42,600
Ready to meet the legends
of B.S. Brothers?

399
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,520
There he is. The first one.

400
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:54,560
Meet Cher, or "Laem"
as everyone calls him.

401
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:56,200
The Comet Mage.

402
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:59,240
He plays Mage,
dealing devastating burst magic damage.

403
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:00,880
Next up...

404
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:03,080
She's Preaw, the Lady General.

405
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:04,320
She plays Carry

406
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:07,960
and is the attack damage carry
the team can't live without.

407
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:09,880
This guy...

408
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:11,280
Jack,

409
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,280
or the Lone Wolf.

410
00:25:14,400 --> 00:25:15,880
He plays as a Dark Slayer Laner

411
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:18,600
specializing in pushing
and keeping the enemies on their toes.

412
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:20,680
And this one right here.

413
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:25,400
He's P'Toobtub,

414
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:28,440
the strategist.
He plans our every single move.

415
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:32,680
And as for me, the King of the Jungle.

416
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,320
A Jungler,

417
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:37,440
the backline diver
with insane farming that enemies fear.

418
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:44,600
And here are the legends
of B.S. Brothers!

419
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:54,880
Hello.

420
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:56,440
My name is Soh.

421
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:57,840
Or...

422
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,480
Or...

423
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:04,160
It's okay, Derpy Kid.
You can think of one later.

424
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:07,920
You're done talking?

425
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:10,840
Hey, Jack.

426
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:13,400
Help me out with the cooking.

427
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:14,320
Move it.

428
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:15,560
Got it.

429
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:20,080
Hey,

430
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:21,760
Preaw.

431
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:23,320
Why didn't you call for help?

432
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:25,440
How can you carry
all these boxes by yourself?

433
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:26,920
P'Three!

434
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,440
Are you just going to
stand there doing nothing?

435
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:32,920
- Come on, there are three boxes.
- Watch your mouth, dude.

436
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,920
Why did you have to say it like that?

437
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,640
Is there anything I can help with?

438
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,240
Nothing.

439
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:07,600
Are you okay, P'Three?

440
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:13,640
You derpy kid.

441
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:15,560
Be more careful.

442
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:36,400
(We are B.S. Brothers)

443
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:57,800
I'm okay now.

444
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:02,640
My friends are just silly like that.

445
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:04,720
You'll get used to them before long.

446
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:10,720
Is it that obvious
that I'm super nervous?

447
00:28:12,040 --> 00:28:12,920
Crystal clear.

448
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:14,720
Like it's written on your forehead.

449
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:43,280
(We are B.S. Brothers)

450
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:14,280
- Numb2r, Numb2r!
- Numb2r, Numb2r!

451
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:17,880
We're number one!

452
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:25,840
Well...

453
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,280
Look at this. What a mess.

454
00:29:28,440 --> 00:29:30,000
Man, who wrote this?

455
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:31,680
Where's P'Three?

456
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:35,520
He should be in the cafe with P'Toobtub.

457
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:40,240
Just think of it as a game.

458
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,920
A super tough level
that you have to clear.

459
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:45,280
I believe that if it's about gaming,

460
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,440
you can definitely beat it.

461
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:48,280
Just like when you got up there
and danced with me.

462
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:56,280
So how did he manage
to trick you into this?

463
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:58,360
He didn't.

464
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:00,320
He didn't trick me.

465
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:05,080
You don't have to be so polite.
We're probably the same age.

466
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:06,760
Right, P'Laem?

467
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:09,120
Yeah, right.

468
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:11,440
Being in B.S. Brothers,

469
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:12,960
you just gotta chill.

470
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:15,400
No need to be so polite or anything.

471
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:15,880
Yeah.

472
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:17,680
Just say, "Preaw, you dumbass!"

473
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:19,040
- Whoa, whoa.
- Just chill.

474
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:22,040
- You got it, P'Cher!
- Hey, what are you doing?

475
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:24,480
Hey, Soh, look at this.
She's a total psycho Carry.

476
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:25,800
- What are you guys doing?
- You want this?

477
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:27,720
- Stop, you psycho Carry!
- Hey, what are you doing?

478
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:29,360
- You're gonna get paint everywhere.
- Bring it on!

479
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,880
- No, no, no.
- Take that!

480
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:38,960
Uh, Preaw did it.

481
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:40,800
No, P'Laem did it.

482
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,280
- Hey, what? I didn't.
- Well, you dodged!

483
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:43,280
You guys are so dead.

484
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:44,920
- Hey, I'm out!
- Get back here!

485
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:47,920
- Wait! What?
- P'Jack, I'm not with them.

486
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,560
- No, you are. Head in the paint!
- So you want this?

487
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:52,280
- Grab him! Put his head in the paint!
- P'Jack, I didn't do anything.

488
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:55,080
- Grab him! Hey, no!
- Man, you're the culprit!

489
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:57,080
- Soh, move out of the way.
- Hey, don't move!

490
00:30:57,120 --> 00:31:00,000
- This has nothing to do with you. Move.
- Stay right there. No, stop!

491
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:01,760
Stop it!

492
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:05,040
Preaw, hey.

493
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,600
Come on.

494
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,000
Bring it.

495
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:14,240
Come on.

496
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:40,920
P'Laem, come here!

497
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,440
Get him! Get him!

498
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,440
Hey, you ready?

499
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:07,080
What should we do with the newbie?

500
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:10,040
- Let's give him a proper welcome!
- Don't mess with him!

501
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:20,880
Stop messing with him.

502
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,120
Oh, you think this is funny?

503
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:30,120
- You're getting it, then.
- Hey, P'Three!

504
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:33,640
Laughing, huh? You think it's funny?

505
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,400
Jeez, what are you guys even doing?

506
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,240
Why the hell are you splashing me?

507
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:41,200
P'Jack, come here! P'Laem, P'Jack!

508
00:32:41,320 --> 00:32:42,360
- Take this.
- Hey, what?

509
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:20,800
We're a mess.

510
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:25,000
P'Toobtub really worked me to the bone.

511
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,880
He kept me painting that wall.
Forget about gaming.

512
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:32,880
Well, well.

513
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:36,000
I'm curious to see
what P'Three's boy's got.

514
00:33:38,640 --> 00:33:39,800
Think you're pretty hot stuff, huh?

515
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:44,520
Come on, let's play a couple of games.

516
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:46,000
- Come on.
- Yeah, okay.

517
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:47,280
- Let's do it.
- 05...

518
00:33:47,320 --> 00:33:48,480
805?

519
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:50,800
- 884.
- 805...

520
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:52,520
- 884
- 80588...

521
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,000
884.

522
00:33:55,320 --> 00:33:56,480
Let's pick our heroes.

523
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:03,640
Let's go. Let's go!

524
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,840
Whoa, you guys actually know
what you're doing.

525
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,480
Of course. We're pros at this.

526
00:34:13,720 --> 00:34:14,680
Do your job, Jungler.

527
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:17,440
(Abyssal Dragon has been defeated)

528
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,520
Soh, where are you going?
You're on the wrong side.

529
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:27,160
I'm on my way.

530
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:30,160
Support, you're not tanking
any damage. Faster.

531
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:33,520
I'm being dove!

532
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,560
I can't hold them off anymore.

533
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,520
The inner turret!

534
00:34:44,720 --> 00:34:46,480
(The Blue Team's tower
has been destroyed)

535
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:47,920
They've got Blade of Eternity.

536
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,160
Ugh, I can't do this anymore.

537
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:56,200
We lost in the league, and now this...

538
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,160
Man, I'm starving.
Let's go grab some food.

539
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:03,680
I'm heading home.
Catch you later.

540
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:05,320
I'm beat today.

541
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:08,520
Exactly. He made me paint so much
I'm getting jacked.

542
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:10,160
Look at this. Look.

543
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,600
- I'm out. Noodles sound good.
- What?

544
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:12,680
Thought we'd play a couple of games.

545
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:14,840
The noodle lady
won't wait forever. Noodles!

546
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:17,760
I was just getting started.

547
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,520
- What is wrong with you guys?
- Catch you later, P'Three!

548
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:21,640
I'm so hungry.

549
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:43,520
So this is the newbie?

550
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:45,880
I don't see what the hype is all about.

551
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,120
Yeah.

552
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:50,400
Three, is the kid you brought

553
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,640
really up for this?

554
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:55,000
Come on, give him some time.

555
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,000
I'll take care of him.

556
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:57,640
Make sure you do.

557
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:13,800
What? Feeling down already?

558
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,960
You scared me, P'Three.

559
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,880
How did you know...

560
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:21,240
Because you're Derpy Kid.

561
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:26,680
You're not exactly subtle.

562
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,040
Don't stress about it. Let's go.

563
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,560
I'll drop you at the train station
when we're done tonight, okay?

564
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,400
Okay?

565
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:56,200
- P'Three...
- Yeah?

566
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:59,840
Actually, you don't have to drop me off.

567
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,400
I can make my own way back.

568
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:04,840
What? Who said I'm dropping you off?

569
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:05,840
I'm...

570
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:09,280
just going to pick some things up.

571
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:10,680
Yeah.

572
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,080
Look at you.

573
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:17,680
I'm kidding.

574
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:19,120
Of course I'm dropping you off.

575
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,520
Since you're so down like this,

576
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:22,360
how could I let you go home alone?

577
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:28,480
P'Three, do you remember
what I told you?

578
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:32,560
I said if I can't handle it,
I'd ask to withdraw, remember?

579
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:37,200
I remember your conditions.

580
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:41,680
I don't think I'm cut out
for the Pro League.

581
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:52,320
But...

582
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:57,760
even if you haven't clicked
with the team yet,

583
00:37:57,800 --> 00:37:59,840
you seem to be opening up more.

584
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,840
That alone is a big achievement.

585
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,920
Any better and you'd have to be me.

586
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:20,320
I'd just hate for you to give up now.

587
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:22,400
If you still want to keep fighting,

588
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:25,160
I want to help you
unlock your own achievements, too.

589
00:38:31,600 --> 00:38:33,520
Let's clear this level together, Soh.

590
00:38:43,280 --> 00:38:44,880
(Why are you tagging us right now?)

591
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:48,600
Hey, I need your help with something.

592
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:51,600
(You're a Pro League player, Soh.)

593
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:53,600
(What do you want us to help you with?)

594
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:55,680
Help me practice RoV.

595
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:59,440
Watch out for the ambush in the Jungle.

596
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:00,720
Hold them off.

597
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:02,920
Take the tower. Now.

598
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:04,640
Nice work up top. Push it. Push.

599
00:39:08,800 --> 00:39:09,920
They lost their inner tower.

600
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:11,720
Looks like they're setting up a gank.

601
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:13,400
Three of them in the bottom lane.

602
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:16,720
(Dare to rematch, you bullsh*tters?)

603
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:20,200
(Newbie, big mouth, trash, noob)

604
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:26,880
Who the hell did this?

605
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:31,920
Just wait until I find out

606
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:34,040
which little brat is behind this.

607
00:39:35,760 --> 00:39:38,360
Is it those backseat gamers
who have beef with you, Laem?

608
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:40,480
You do love pwning those brats.

609
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,880
I don't think so.

610
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:57,960
(Newbie)

611
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,760
Don't read those things.

612
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:08,040
Just look at me.

613
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:24,040
Look, they even left their tag
on the wall.

614
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,280
Jeez!

615
00:40:29,560 --> 00:40:31,440
Should we call the cops on them?

616
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:34,320
No need.
Those backseat gamers are pathetic.

617
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:36,760
Yeah, I'm with P'Toobtub on this.

618
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:38,680
This doesn't need the police.

619
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:43,120
Three, where are you going?

620
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,200
Isn't it obvious?

621
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:47,280
I'm going to...

622
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:51,720
deal with them myself. Damn it!

623
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:54,680
- Let's go, Laem. Come with me.
- Let's go, yeah. Let's do it.

624
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:57,560
- Why would you bring that chair?
- Well...

625
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:58,880
- Go!
- Come on.

626
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,560
- Give me the key.
- Alright, move it.

627
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:02,880
Wait up!

628
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:05,480
Kids, why the hell did you do that?

629
00:41:07,720 --> 00:41:10,240
I'm an only child of my parents,
not your kid.

630
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:13,240
Don't blame us
for teaching you a lesson, then.

631
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:14,800
Don't go crying to your dad
about it, either.

632
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,720
Is that what you did all the time
when you were a kid?

633
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:18,160
Is that why you think we'd do the same?

634
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:21,640
You've got guts, Pod,
challenging a Pro League team.

635
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,080
I don't care how good you are

636
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:25,120
as long as you have
such dead weight on your team.

637
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:32,480
That's what you think, too, isn't it?

638
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,040
You just haven't said it out loud.

639
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:35,040
Go on, say it.

640
00:41:35,040 --> 00:41:35,960
Exactly.

641
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:39,840
What are you talking about?

642
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:42,000
Nobody's thinking anything like that.

643
00:41:44,520 --> 00:41:46,240
Yeah, right now,

644
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:48,400
our team might not have
quite gelled yet...

645
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:51,280
But when it comes to
crushing toxic brats like you,

646
00:41:51,640 --> 00:41:53,640
it'll be a total piece of cake.

647
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:56,560
We'll see about that.

648
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:59,080
How about this? Let's do a best-of-five.

649
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:04,080
And if we win...

650
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:05,960
You have to repaint P'Toobtub's cafe

651
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,280
and make it look as good as new.

652
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:10,000
And apologize to us, too.

653
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:11,680
- Deal?
- Fine.

654
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:12,960
But if we win,

655
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,280
you have to leave the team

656
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:16,360
and let us join B.S. Brothers instead.

657
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:17,360
Is that a deal?

658
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:24,480
Deal?

659
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:25,520
Deal.

660
00:42:27,640 --> 00:42:30,320
- Let's show them what we've got.
- Yeah, bring it on.

661
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:33,840
(The Blue Team's tower
has been destroyed)

662
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:37,400
(Infinite Slayer has been defeated)

663
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:38,920
Sh*t, it's an ambush.

664
00:42:46,080 --> 00:42:46,520
(The Red Team's tower
has been destroyed)

665
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:49,000
Keep pushing. Push it.

666
00:42:50,440 --> 00:42:51,800
- Nice!
- Nice.

667
00:42:51,840 --> 00:42:53,240
(Infinite Slayer has been summoned)
(Vanguard is advancing)

668
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:55,880
- Wrap it up!
- They're dead.

669
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:57,040
(The Red Team's tower
has been destroyed)

670
00:42:57,680 --> 00:42:59,040
- Alright.
- Hey, hey, hey!

671
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:10,680
You're f*cking legendary, my Derya MK12.

672
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:14,240
Hey, hey, hey!

673
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:17,960
Keep your end of the deal, Pod.

674
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:23,440
I'm sorry.

675
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:27,120
What? I didn't catch that.
Say it again.

676
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:28,800
I said I'm sorry.

677
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:30,160
What more do you want, P'Laem?

678
00:43:31,360 --> 00:43:33,120
You shouldn't just be
apologizing to me.

679
00:43:34,240 --> 00:43:35,720
You need to apologize to everyone

680
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:37,640
for tagging P'Toobtub's wall like that.

681
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:41,000
Do you have any idea
how exhausting it was to paint that?

682
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,280
I'm sorry.

683
00:43:45,280 --> 00:43:47,640
I'm sorry, P'Toobtub,
for tagging the wall.

684
00:43:47,640 --> 00:43:48,280
And...

685
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:50,760
I'm sorry
for looking down on you, P'Soh.

686
00:43:51,160 --> 00:43:52,680
It was an honest mistake.

687
00:43:52,880 --> 00:43:54,000
That excuse again.

688
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:57,800
I'll forgive you guys,

689
00:43:58,160 --> 00:44:00,120
but don't you go
doing this to anyone else.

690
00:44:00,400 --> 00:44:02,320
They would've called the cops on you.

691
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:05,240
- Come on, we already said we're sorry.
- We're sorry.

692
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:06,280
I didn't mean any harm.

693
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:08,040
We practiced so hard

694
00:44:08,040 --> 00:44:09,320
for that audition, though.

695
00:44:09,400 --> 00:44:10,720
You never got back to us

696
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:13,160
after you said you'd call, right?

697
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:15,560
- Yeah.
- Then you just went and picked P'Soh.

698
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:17,400
But he is legit good, man.

699
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:18,720
Yeah, he is.

700
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,560
Sh*t, you guys play like trash.

701
00:44:20,680 --> 00:44:22,560
Look, you are just kids.

702
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:24,160
If you want my advice,

703
00:44:24,160 --> 00:44:26,480
you can be subs
for B.S. Brothers for now.

704
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:28,800
And if you improve,
I'll let you play in the big leagues.

705
00:44:30,880 --> 00:44:31,880
- Really?
- For real?

706
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:33,400
- You mean it?
- Thank you so much.

707
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:34,560
Thank you.

708
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:36,520
Yeah, yeah.

709
00:44:36,560 --> 00:44:38,200
- We're glad to be on the team.
- Look forward to learning from you.

710
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:39,320
Look forward to playing with you.

711
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:43,720
Yeah, give it a try.

712
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:46,600
Let's give them a chance.

713
00:44:47,320 --> 00:44:48,360
Gotta give people a chance, man.

714
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:50,760
I'll give it my all.

715
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:01,560
A large mookrata set is here!

716
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:03,600
Look, you go serve the drinks.

717
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:06,160
Hey, can someone
grab a tray for the pork?

718
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:07,200
I'll go get it.

719
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:07,760
Alright.

720
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:12,800
- Here's the extension cord.
- Finally found the stove. Took me ages.

721
00:45:13,680 --> 00:45:15,000
It was right there in the storage.

722
00:45:15,040 --> 00:45:16,880
Here. Use this for the sauces.

723
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:19,120
P'Toobtub, what do you want to drink?

724
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:21,000
Get me some toilet water
with two ice cubes.

725
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:22,880
Toilet water with ice?
Go drink it over there.

726
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:25,480
(Dare to rematch, you bullsh*tters?)

727
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:27,720
(Newbie, big mouth, trash, noob)

728
00:45:27,720 --> 00:45:29,600
(Only got in
'cause they were short-handed)

729
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:44,040
With the weather this nice,

730
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:46,120
let's get some exercise
before hitting the mookrata.

731
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:47,120
Hurry up, come on.

732
00:45:48,720 --> 00:45:49,720
Move it.

733
00:45:49,720 --> 00:45:51,480
- Go on, move over.
- Put it down. Put the paint down.

734
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:54,080
- The paint is right here.
- Hey.

735
00:45:54,640 --> 00:45:55,560
How can you paint
all of this by yourself?

736
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:57,520
- I'll cover the black paint.
- We'll all help you.

737
00:45:58,640 --> 00:45:59,920
It's all over.

738
00:46:01,720 --> 00:46:02,960
Come on, don't just stand there talking.

739
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:04,800
- The job won't finish itself.
- You won't stop talking.

740
00:46:07,520 --> 00:46:08,200
Got it?

741
00:46:41,680 --> 00:46:42,560
You're getting the paint all over me!

742
00:46:42,600 --> 00:46:43,680
Sorry, sorry.

743
00:46:43,880 --> 00:46:45,600
Hey, newbie, refill the paint.

744
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:48,080
Everyone, cheers!

745
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:53,240
That was so satisfying!

746
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:55,160
I know they were just some kids,

747
00:46:55,200 --> 00:46:57,720
but how long has it been
since our team won?

748
00:46:57,720 --> 00:46:58,640
- Exactly.
- Right.

749
00:46:58,640 --> 00:47:00,800
I didn't think
you'd be this serious, Soh.

750
00:47:01,120 --> 00:47:02,640
You look all quiet and innocent,

751
00:47:02,960 --> 00:47:04,760
but you're an absolute beast.

752
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:06,040
You're a beast.

753
00:47:08,680 --> 00:47:10,960
Well, you all worked so hard
to finish painting the wall.

754
00:47:11,360 --> 00:47:13,520
If all your hard work went to waste
because of me,

755
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:14,920
I would have felt terrible.

756
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:16,880
That's why we had to win.

757
00:47:18,720 --> 00:47:20,560
Soh, what shirt size do you wear?

758
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:23,360
Judging by your build,
you're not that big.

759
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:24,600
I'll get you a team jersey.

760
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:25,880
Thanks.

761
00:47:25,920 --> 00:47:28,800
Our team used to be
just a bunch of chubby guys.

762
00:47:29,160 --> 00:47:29,960
- Hey.
- Hey.

763
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:31,200
Well, look what you feed us.

764
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:32,520
Look at all this stuff.

765
00:47:32,520 --> 00:47:34,600
Here, Soh, I grilled this just for you.

766
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:36,400
Chicken breast is good for you.

767
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:37,200
Go ahead, have some.

768
00:47:37,240 --> 00:47:38,280
- Hey!
- Hey!

769
00:47:38,440 --> 00:47:39,640
What's up with that?

770
00:47:39,840 --> 00:47:40,800
How could you do this?

771
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:42,800
You used to be feeding me.

772
00:47:42,800 --> 00:47:44,120
Yeah, and look at you now.

773
00:47:44,200 --> 00:47:45,920
Man, I should file a property claim.

774
00:47:45,920 --> 00:47:46,440
Exactly.

775
00:47:46,480 --> 00:47:47,720
Because that spot next to him

776
00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:49,720
used to be ours.

777
00:47:52,560 --> 00:47:54,160
And why are you whining, too?

778
00:47:58,280 --> 00:47:59,040
Guys.

779
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:05,280
Actually, I have an idea
for renovating P'Toobtub's cafe.

780
00:48:06,080 --> 00:48:07,040
I think...

781
00:48:07,920 --> 00:48:11,520
the cafe should have
more food and lounge areas.

782
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:16,040
When delivery riders come
to pick up or drop off food,

783
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:17,400
they'll have a place to wait.

784
00:48:18,040 --> 00:48:21,680
Plus, we'd attract customers
who aren't just gamers.

785
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:25,160
Hey, that's a great idea, Soh.

786
00:48:25,280 --> 00:48:25,840
I'm sold.

787
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:27,280
Thanks a lot.

788
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:29,920
Yeah, that's a good idea.

789
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:33,000
Your cafe has been around forever.
It really needs a renovation.

790
00:48:33,440 --> 00:48:34,360
For real.

791
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:37,240
It's like your cafe's
still stuck in the Numb2r era.

792
00:48:50,240 --> 00:48:51,200
Is it cooked yet?

793
00:48:51,360 --> 00:48:52,560
It's taking forever.

794
00:48:57,880 --> 00:48:58,760
Uh...

795
